linesize(int) - Method in class org.bytedeco.ffmpeg.avutil.AVFrame
For video, a positive or negative value, which is typically indicating the size in bytes of each picture line, but it can also be: - the negative byte size of lines for vertical flipping (with data[n] pointing to the end of the data - a positive or negative multiple of the byte size as for accessing even and odd fields of a frame (possibly flipped) For audio, only linesize[0] may be set.
